Day#02 - Understanding VR tracking and performance

Frame Rate - 
--Frame rate is the number of images(frames) displayed per second on the screen. Its unit if FPS(Frames Per Second). In virutal reality high framerate is very essential
as if the framerate drops too low, the virtual world may lag behind the user's movement, which can lead to discomfot or motion sickeness.
--For Virtual reality, the comfortable frame rate is between 90-110 as it causes smooth movements and low latency. 

Tracking -

1) Inside-out tracking -
--Inside-out tracking is a tracking method in which the cameras and sensors are attached in the headset itself, 
--These cameras observe surrounding environment and use it as reference points to deternmine the headset's movement and postion is realtime.

Advantages - 
--Easy to set up
--No external cameras or setup required

Disadvantages - 
--Tracking accuracy can decrease if the cameras or sensors can't see the surroundings clear(Ex. in darkness)
--Controllers may lose tracking if they move out of the camera's field of view.


2)Outside-in tracking - 
--Outside-in tracking is a tracking method in which there are external cameras and sensors which are placed around the play area.
--These cameras externally track the physical movements of the headset and controller and track it in the virtaul world.

Advantages - 
--As the cameras and sensors are external, the tracking is highly acurrate and precise.
--Commonly used in professional VR setups and is usually better for large movements

Disadvantages - 
--Requires external cameras and sensors
--Takes longer to setup and less portable

Conclusion - 
I learnt that smooth vr experience not only requires powerful hardware but also and accurate tracking of headset and controllers and high frame rates. I understood these different types 
of tracking which are inside-out and outside-in tracking and their pros and cons. If you value convenience and easy setup then inside-out tracking and if you want maximum precision and ultra
low latency then outside-in tracking is superior.


